      The 1860 Slave Schedule for Clarke County, Alabama records Primus Armstead under the household
      of C. Armstead — establishing pre-1862 enslaved status, the foundational requirement for
      Freedmen Nation verification and FRFT eligibility. This is a primary source with a direct
      evidentiary link to the proband through a continuous documentary chain.
